      • setArrowPosition

        public boolean setArrowPosition(ProcessorDiagram pro1,
                                ProcessorDiagram pro2,
                                Arrow.cycleType type,
                                java.lang.String register,
                                int offset)
        Sets arrow position according to ProcessDiagram, cycle type, register name and offset value. Or off screen if processor diagram level difference if not 1 or 2.
        Parameters:
        pro1 - Processor diagram the arrow starts from.
        pro2 - Processor diagram the arrow goes to.
        type - Type of the cycle.
        register - Register the arrow goes to. Usually rs or rt.
        offset - The offset on x position.
        Returns:
        true if processor level difference is 1 or 2, false otherwise.
